1
00:00:01,760 --> 00:00:04,000
That woman has to be
connected to me somehow.

2
00:00:04,800 --> 00:00:06,080
That's why we need her help.

3
00:00:06,160 --> 00:00:09,160
<i>As for helping Sin like Mrs. Wanee asked,</i>

4
00:00:09,240 --> 00:00:11,360
I'll have to find a way
to turn it down again.

5
00:00:11,440 --> 00:00:14,520
No. You have to keep working for me.

6
00:00:15,320 --> 00:00:16,840
<i>Maybe Ms. Mysterious</i>

7
00:00:17,840 --> 00:00:19,880
has been waiting for both of you.

8
00:00:21,600 --> 00:00:24,840
Mom, this is Aunt Anong,
my biological aunt.

9
00:00:24,920 --> 00:00:25,920
And this is Uncle Sarut,

10
00:00:26,840 --> 00:00:28,520
my uncle-in-law.

11
00:00:28,600 --> 00:00:29,880
Hello, ma'am.

12
00:00:32,360 --> 00:00:34,360
Jirasin's important guest?

13
00:00:36,600 --> 00:00:38,400
I think there's definitely
something hidden,

14
00:00:39,320 --> 00:00:41,000
some ulterior motive.

15
00:00:43,320 --> 00:00:47,080
That's why he brings strangers
into an event like this.

16
00:00:47,760 --> 00:00:50,320
I think we shouldn't
get involved with them.

17
00:00:50,400 --> 00:00:52,880
If they really intend
to make a scene here,

18
00:00:52,960 --> 00:00:56,200
they might actually be satisfied
if they succeed.

19
00:00:56,280 --> 00:00:58,040
I think we should just stay out of it.

20
00:00:58,640 --> 00:01:00,080
I'm not good at putting on an act.

21
00:01:00,600 --> 00:01:02,720
Please trust me just once.

22
00:01:02,800 --> 00:01:05,280
Don't get involved with them.
Let's stay here.

23
00:01:07,280 --> 00:01:08,280
Hey.

24
00:01:16,720 --> 00:01:18,760
Prae, listen to me. Prae.

25
00:01:18,840 --> 00:01:22,800
Prae, Prae. Come on, Prae. Don't do this.

26
00:01:22,880 --> 00:01:25,480
Don't be mad at me, please. Don't be mad.

27
00:01:26,200 --> 00:01:27,080
Prae?

28
00:01:28,680 --> 00:01:30,360
This is way beyond just being mad.

29
00:01:31,040 --> 00:01:32,560
You deliberately deceived me.

30
00:01:32,640 --> 00:01:35,600
I never deceived you.
And I never intended to deceive you, Prae.

31
00:01:36,200 --> 00:01:38,520
I love you.
But I told you from the beginning

32
00:01:38,600 --> 00:01:41,600
that I'm already with someone.

33
00:01:41,680 --> 00:01:44,760
That's not true.
You never told me directly.

34
00:01:44,840 --> 00:01:47,720
Prae, calm down.
Please listen to me first.

35
00:01:47,800 --> 00:01:49,560
I love you so much. I really love you.

36
00:01:54,320 --> 00:01:55,680
You deceived me.

37
00:01:55,760 --> 00:01:57,440
The baby in my womb,

38
00:01:58,200 --> 00:01:59,600
I won't keep it.

39
00:01:59,680 --> 00:02:02,040
And I'll kill you too!

40
00:02:02,120 --> 00:02:03,480
- Prae!
- Do you understand?!

41
00:02:03,560 --> 00:02:05,480
Why would you do this to me?

42
00:02:05,560 --> 00:02:07,000
Why did you deceive me like this?

43
00:02:07,080 --> 00:02:08,720
- Prae!
- Stop it, Sarut.

44
00:02:10,440 --> 00:02:11,840
Ms. Mysterious?

45
00:02:11,920 --> 00:02:15,280
If you touch Prae one more time,
I'll tell Wichan everything.

46
00:02:15,360 --> 00:02:16,680
Shut up, you low-class woman.

47
00:02:17,280 --> 00:02:19,280
You think you can do
anything to me, Ampha?

48
00:02:19,360 --> 00:02:20,840
Get away from here. Prae.

49
00:02:22,320 --> 00:02:23,640
Of course I can.

50
00:02:23,720 --> 00:02:26,280
But I've never thought
of harassing anyone the way you did.

51
00:02:26,960 --> 00:02:29,440
Your actions are lower than low.

52
00:02:31,160 --> 00:02:33,040
Hey! Let go!

53
00:02:33,120 --> 00:02:34,800
- So mouthy, aren't you?
- Let go!

54
00:02:35,760 --> 00:02:38,120
<i>Kluay. Kluay.</i>

55
00:02:41,800 --> 00:02:42,720
Kluay.

56
00:02:51,560 --> 00:02:52,600
Kluay.

57
00:02:55,080 --> 00:02:57,440
- Mr. Warat.
- What did you see?

58
00:03:00,640 --> 00:03:03,560
I… I can't explain it properly.

59
00:03:04,160 --> 00:03:05,280
So you saw something.

60
00:03:09,480 --> 00:03:10,680
If you're not feeling well, wanna go rest?

61
00:03:12,000 --> 00:03:15,080
I'll have someone take you home, okay?

62
00:03:15,160 --> 00:03:16,120
Okay.

63
00:03:16,840 --> 00:03:17,920
Hello.

64
00:03:24,360 --> 00:03:25,600
Are you Warat?

65
00:03:26,840 --> 00:03:29,560
I'm Sarut, a friend of your dad's.

66
00:03:31,480 --> 00:03:33,080
Thank you for coming.

67
00:03:33,160 --> 00:03:34,120
Wait a moment.

68
00:03:36,400 --> 00:03:38,240
I didn't see you around much.

69
00:03:38,320 --> 00:03:41,720
I thought maybe
you studied abroad for many years.

70
00:03:42,600 --> 00:03:44,680
Well, I don't recall
my dad ever mentioning you.

71
00:03:45,480 --> 00:03:46,920
Maybe that's because…

72
00:03:49,080 --> 00:03:50,320
I was ill.

73
00:03:50,920 --> 00:03:53,760
I couldn't go anywhere,
so I drifted apart from your dad.

74
00:03:54,480 --> 00:03:57,480
What illness do you have, sir?

75
00:03:57,560 --> 00:04:00,120
Maybe wait until we're closer
before talking about that?

76
00:04:00,800 --> 00:04:02,560
Uh, I choose who I'm close with.

77
00:04:03,600 --> 00:04:06,080
It's nothing, sir. I only asked because

78
00:04:06,680 --> 00:04:08,640
if you were truly close to my dad,

79
00:04:08,720 --> 00:04:10,160
I'd like to know

80
00:04:10,240 --> 00:04:12,920
any information related to him.

81
00:04:13,000 --> 00:04:14,720
- So I could ask.
- Mm.

82
00:04:14,800 --> 00:04:18,360
If there's nothing, then sorry about that.

83
00:04:19,880 --> 00:04:22,440
Why be sorry? There's no need.

84
00:04:23,640 --> 00:04:26,240
It's just an illness.
I can talk about it. It's no secret.

85
00:04:27,480 --> 00:04:29,400
I'm like this…

86
00:04:37,080 --> 00:04:39,040
because I was in a car accident.

87
00:04:41,200 --> 00:04:42,800
So this is how I am now.

88
00:04:45,680 --> 00:04:49,280
We'll excuse ourselves now, because

89
00:04:49,360 --> 00:04:52,240
he's very talkative.

90
00:04:52,320 --> 00:04:54,840
Otherwise, the conversation
will drift all over the place,

91
00:04:54,920 --> 00:04:56,800
and you won't get to greet the guests.

92
00:04:57,800 --> 00:05:01,560
But it's nice to meet you.

93
00:05:01,640 --> 00:05:03,680
Likewise. Please.

94
00:05:05,400 --> 00:05:07,120
I'm sure we'll meet again soon.

95
00:05:26,400 --> 00:05:28,640
Keep a close eye on Jirasin.

96
00:05:28,720 --> 00:05:30,760
Why did he never tell me

97
00:05:30,840 --> 00:05:34,680
that he has both an aunt
and an uncle-in-law like that?

98
00:05:34,760 --> 00:05:36,040
Yes, ma'am.

99
00:05:36,120 --> 00:05:38,720
But if she is Mr. Jirasin's aunt,

100
00:05:38,800 --> 00:05:41,040
then that means she's Ms. Naree's sister.

101
00:05:41,760 --> 00:05:43,600
Naree, Jirasin's mother?

102
00:05:43,680 --> 00:05:45,160
Yes, ma'am.

103
00:05:46,400 --> 00:05:48,640
She drove herself to death.

104
00:05:50,120 --> 00:05:51,320
It's all my fault.

105
00:05:51,400 --> 00:05:54,560
Perhaps you should
get in the car first, ma'am.

106
00:05:54,640 --> 00:05:57,040
I'll report back about those two later.

107
00:05:57,120 --> 00:06:02,720
This matter will probably haunt me
until the day I die.

108
00:06:03,320 --> 00:06:05,720
With the utmost respect, ma'am,

109
00:06:05,800 --> 00:06:09,640
from the past until now,
you've already paid more than enough.

110
00:06:09,720 --> 00:06:11,640
But there must be something

111
00:06:12,920 --> 00:06:17,360
that made those two
choose to appear at today's ceremony.

112
00:06:25,000 --> 00:06:28,480
Please come inside first.
I'll go get some water.

113
00:06:28,560 --> 00:06:32,080
It's alright.
I just wanted to see you safely home,

114
00:06:32,160 --> 00:06:34,200
for my own peace of mind.

115
00:06:34,280 --> 00:06:37,240
If this were before,
your words might have shocked me.

116
00:06:37,880 --> 00:06:38,880
But now,

117
00:06:40,040 --> 00:06:40,960
I'm used to them.

118
00:06:41,040 --> 00:06:43,880
Why? Did I say something wrong?

119
00:06:46,840 --> 00:06:50,000
If there's nothing else,
please go back and rest.

120
00:06:50,080 --> 00:06:52,360
You've been exhausted from work all day.

121
00:06:52,440 --> 00:06:54,000
Mmm.

122
00:06:54,080 --> 00:06:55,800
And you had to drive me home.

123
00:06:56,960 --> 00:06:58,320
Thank you so much.

124
00:06:58,400 --> 00:06:59,840
I'm not going back yet.

125
00:07:00,520 --> 00:07:02,280
I'll stay until you're feeling better.

126
00:07:03,240 --> 00:07:04,200
Oh.

127
00:07:04,920 --> 00:07:07,560
You don't need to worry
about me that much.

128
00:07:08,480 --> 00:07:10,120
I'd say it's more like guilt.

129
00:07:10,920 --> 00:07:12,520
Because you worked for me,

130
00:07:13,040 --> 00:07:14,360
that's why you get sick like this.

131
00:07:15,040 --> 00:07:16,160
Oh.

132
00:07:16,240 --> 00:07:18,520
So you're not actually worried about me.

133
00:07:20,520 --> 00:07:23,520
But the main reason I'm staying

134
00:07:24,280 --> 00:07:27,200
is because I want to ask you what you saw.

135
00:07:33,120 --> 00:07:35,160
The way you're looking right now

136
00:07:36,720 --> 00:07:37,960
means you really saw something.

137
00:07:41,280 --> 00:07:43,040
You deliberately deceived me.

138
00:07:43,840 --> 00:07:44,760
Well,

139
00:07:45,520 --> 00:07:49,080
I saw a woman named Praewilai.

140
00:07:49,680 --> 00:07:50,920
Mom?

141
00:07:52,600 --> 00:07:53,720
Yes.

142
00:07:54,920 --> 00:07:55,920
Did you see my dad too?

143
00:07:57,960 --> 00:08:01,080
But I told you from the beginning
that I'm already with someone.

144
00:08:01,960 --> 00:08:03,680
The baby in my womb,

145
00:08:04,520 --> 00:08:06,240
I won't keep it.

146
00:08:06,320 --> 00:08:10,040
I'll kill it, and then I'll kill you too!

147
00:08:12,120 --> 00:08:13,120
Mr. Warat,

148
00:08:13,800 --> 00:08:16,640
about your father…

149
00:08:26,720 --> 00:08:28,000
Mr. Sarut,

150
00:08:29,680 --> 00:08:31,840
my dad, and my mom.

151
00:08:33,039 --> 00:08:34,960
They all know each other?

152
00:08:35,039 --> 00:08:36,720
It seems that way.

153
00:08:37,400 --> 00:08:39,880
But I didn't see your dad.

154
00:08:39,960 --> 00:08:42,760
I only saw Mr. Sarut and Ms. Praewilai.

155
00:08:43,480 --> 00:08:44,640
Mr. Sarut…

156
00:08:45,640 --> 00:08:47,360
Jirasin's uncle-in-law.

157
00:08:49,600 --> 00:08:50,880
He and my mom were…

158
00:08:51,640 --> 00:08:54,640
Oh, I also saw Ms. Mysterious.

159
00:08:54,720 --> 00:08:58,200
She seemed to love your mom very much.

160
00:08:58,800 --> 00:09:00,800
That woman loved my mom so much,

161
00:09:00,880 --> 00:09:02,360
yet she married my dad?

162
00:09:03,520 --> 00:09:04,680
Uh…

163
00:09:04,760 --> 00:09:07,840
That's something
we'll have to find the answer to.

164
00:09:07,920 --> 00:09:12,960
But I saw that
Ms. Praewilai and Mr. Sarut were arguing.

165
00:09:13,040 --> 00:09:15,040
And Ms. Mysterious
stepped in to stop them.

166
00:09:16,080 --> 00:09:17,360
What were they arguing about?

167
00:09:22,000 --> 00:09:24,040
I…

168
00:09:24,120 --> 00:09:27,040
I couldn't really piece it all together,

169
00:09:27,120 --> 00:09:28,560
so I didn't quite understand.

170
00:09:33,600 --> 00:09:35,080
Are you going to tell me the truth,

171
00:09:35,720 --> 00:09:38,480
or are you going to make me
find out the truth myself

172
00:09:38,560 --> 00:09:40,080
and we never see each other again?

173
00:09:40,160 --> 00:09:41,800
Hey, you can't do that.

174
00:09:41,880 --> 00:09:43,520
What about Ms. Mysterious?

175
00:09:43,600 --> 00:09:46,200
I already promised her that I'd help her.

176
00:09:46,280 --> 00:09:49,200
If you won't help,
how am I supposed to help her?

177
00:09:49,280 --> 00:09:51,480
What were they arguing about?

178
00:09:56,360 --> 00:09:58,160
I'm sorry, everyone.

179
00:09:58,240 --> 00:10:00,880
If I'm wrong about anything,
you don't have to tell me.

180
00:10:00,960 --> 00:10:01,840
Kluay.

181
00:10:03,280 --> 00:10:05,200
Alright, fine. I'll tell you.

182
00:10:05,280 --> 00:10:08,840
Ms. Praewilai and Mr. Sarut

183
00:10:09,440 --> 00:10:11,080
were arguing about a baby.

184
00:10:13,920 --> 00:10:16,640
- About a baby?
- Yes.

185
00:10:17,440 --> 00:10:20,240
Ms. Praewilai was pregnant.

186
00:10:24,400 --> 00:10:27,360
I don't think
we can talk about this anymore.

187
00:10:27,440 --> 00:10:28,520
Is she here?

188
00:10:31,800 --> 00:10:35,600
Not yet. But she will be
if we don't stop talking about this.

189
00:10:35,680 --> 00:10:39,320
I think Ms. Mysterious doesn't want us
to talk about this.

190
00:10:39,400 --> 00:10:41,760
Otherwise,
I would've told you a long time ago.

191
00:10:42,400 --> 00:10:44,440
Then how am I
supposed to know who you are,

192
00:10:44,520 --> 00:10:46,240
and what really happened to my mom?

193
00:10:46,800 --> 00:10:48,040
So what exactly do you want?

194
00:10:48,120 --> 00:10:49,720
Oh. Uh…

195
00:10:49,800 --> 00:10:53,000
Mr. Warat, don't talk to her like that.

196
00:10:53,080 --> 00:10:54,760
I'm asking. What do you want?

197
00:10:59,880 --> 00:11:00,880
Are you asking me?

198
00:11:19,840 --> 00:11:21,400
Aren't you going to take a shower?

199
00:11:21,480 --> 00:11:23,480
Kids grow up so fast these days.

200
00:11:24,200 --> 00:11:26,280
Look at Warat, so handsome.

201
00:11:27,560 --> 00:11:28,680
All grown up.

202
00:11:34,440 --> 00:11:36,320
Praising him won't change anything.

203
00:11:37,200 --> 00:11:39,960
- He doesn't care about you at all.
- Oh.

204
00:11:40,040 --> 00:11:41,880
Well, he doesn't know me.

205
00:11:42,800 --> 00:11:44,760
You can't really blame him.

206
00:11:46,920 --> 00:11:49,280
I've waited for him for over ten years.

207
00:11:50,240 --> 00:11:53,400
Maybe I'll need some time
to get to know him.

208
00:11:54,240 --> 00:11:57,400
It's not that hard. I can wait.

209
00:11:58,520 --> 00:12:00,600
I'll be supporting you.

210
00:12:02,840 --> 00:12:07,080
And you're right, time really does fly.

211
00:12:07,160 --> 00:12:09,600
In the blink of an eye,
the kids have grown up.

212
00:12:11,280 --> 00:12:15,760
Now Sin and Mr. Warat are close by.

213
00:12:16,640 --> 00:12:18,840
Sooner or later,
they'll probably grow close too.

214
00:12:19,480 --> 00:12:20,640
Yeah.

215
00:12:20,720 --> 00:12:22,720
Who said I'd ever get close
to someone like Warat?

216
00:12:29,280 --> 00:12:30,360
Sin.

217
00:12:31,200 --> 00:12:33,120
Don't talk about Warat like that.

218
00:12:34,400 --> 00:12:36,800
What's the big deal?
I'm about to lose my patience.

219
00:12:37,360 --> 00:12:39,120
Why should I have to cater to him?

220
00:12:39,200 --> 00:12:42,760
Sin, what do you gain
from arguing with him?

221
00:12:42,840 --> 00:12:45,360
We're family.

222
00:12:45,960 --> 00:12:49,800
I don't consider Uncle Rut family.

223
00:12:50,520 --> 00:12:51,920
How can you say that?

224
00:12:52,000 --> 00:12:54,480
He raised you since you were little.

225
00:12:54,560 --> 00:12:56,400
Then you should know this, Aunt Anong.

226
00:12:56,480 --> 00:12:58,240
I've endured Uncle Rut long enough.

227
00:12:58,320 --> 00:13:00,480
Before, I could tolerate it.
But not anymore.

228
00:13:00,560 --> 00:13:03,360
Now that Warat is back,
Uncle Narut keeps talking about him.

229
00:13:03,440 --> 00:13:06,000
I can't take it. I'm disgusted.
I'm going to throw up.

230
00:13:15,680 --> 00:13:18,160
I'm still upset.

231
00:13:18,240 --> 00:13:21,120
I don't know why the flight
had to be delayed today.

232
00:13:21,200 --> 00:13:22,280
That's why

233
00:13:22,360 --> 00:13:25,360
I couldn't make it
to Uncle Wichan's 100-day merit ceremony.

234
00:13:25,440 --> 00:13:26,960
I'm really sorry, Grandma.

235
00:13:27,040 --> 00:13:28,560
It's alright.

236
00:13:28,640 --> 00:13:32,480
You and your father already came
to the wake and the cremation.

237
00:13:32,560 --> 00:13:35,080
That's more than enough for me.

238
00:13:38,000 --> 00:13:40,120
Oh, Warat.

239
00:13:41,120 --> 00:13:42,360
You're back already?

240
00:13:42,440 --> 00:13:44,360
I've been waiting for you.

241
00:13:45,120 --> 00:13:49,120
She really wanted to come
to your dad's 100-day merit ceremony,

242
00:13:49,200 --> 00:13:50,720
but she didn't make it in time.

243
00:13:51,600 --> 00:13:52,560
Thank you.

244
00:13:54,880 --> 00:13:58,320
Stay and talk for a bit.
I still have some work to finish.

245
00:13:59,240 --> 00:14:00,320
Goodbye, Grandma.

246
00:14:00,400 --> 00:14:02,040
- Alright. Take care.
- Yes.

247
00:14:11,640 --> 00:14:13,720
You should go home. I'm tired.

248
00:14:13,800 --> 00:14:15,920
If you're tired,

249
00:14:16,000 --> 00:14:19,120
how about I take you somewhere
to listen to some relaxing music?

250
00:14:19,200 --> 00:14:21,960
If you want to talk business
with my grandmother,

251
00:14:22,040 --> 00:14:24,480
you can come to the office,
or come to the house and talk.

252
00:14:24,560 --> 00:14:27,120
But don't drag me into it. It's pointless.

253
00:14:28,000 --> 00:14:30,720
Are you still mad at me?

254
00:14:32,480 --> 00:14:36,480
Come on, Warat.
It's been almost ten years.

255
00:14:37,920 --> 00:14:40,160
Isn't that what they say

256
00:14:40,240 --> 00:14:43,800
the angrier you are, the more you care?

257
00:14:43,880 --> 00:14:45,440
You should go.

258
00:14:45,520 --> 00:14:47,680
If you stay, I might say something rude.

259
00:14:52,520 --> 00:14:53,920
Stay arrogant as long as you like.

260
00:14:54,440 --> 00:14:58,600
As if I'd ever date that nerd Warat?

261
00:14:58,680 --> 00:15:00,440
Ugh, that gives me chills.

262
00:15:01,160 --> 00:15:03,240
Then why are you walking
around his Vanich Mall?

263
00:15:04,320 --> 00:15:08,400
I thought you were supporting
your future family business.

264
00:15:08,480 --> 00:15:10,880
Hey. My dad forced me.

265
00:15:10,960 --> 00:15:13,200
Ever heard of connections?
Oh, you wouldn't.

266
00:15:14,080 --> 00:15:17,320
Why didn't Grandma cut off the deal
with Ameena's Grand Mall Group?

267
00:15:21,480 --> 00:15:22,480
Arnon.

268
00:15:23,640 --> 00:15:24,680
Are you listening?

269
00:15:24,760 --> 00:15:27,520
Yes, I'm listening.

270
00:15:28,320 --> 00:15:31,920
I'll give you an update tomorrow.
You should get some sleep.

271
00:15:32,600 --> 00:15:34,400
I don't want to see that woman again.

272
00:15:34,920 --> 00:15:39,120
Do whatever it takes to keep
the Grand Mall Group away from Vanich.

273
00:15:40,000 --> 00:15:42,560
It's not that simple.
They're about to merge.

274
00:15:42,640 --> 00:15:45,160
And you're just letting that happen?

275
00:15:45,240 --> 00:15:47,360
Legal matters
are in your hands, aren't they?

276
00:15:48,400 --> 00:15:49,960
Go deal with it.

277
00:15:50,040 --> 00:15:52,960
Hey, I'm a lawyer. I'm not the mall owner.

278
00:15:53,040 --> 00:15:55,000
You are. You deal with it.

279
00:15:55,080 --> 00:15:57,320
I don't want to work with my grandmother.

280
00:15:57,400 --> 00:15:59,080
But you have to.

281
00:15:59,960 --> 00:16:01,200
Listen to me.

282
00:16:02,080 --> 00:16:05,280
If you're going to handle this,
I'll back you up all the way.

283
00:16:05,880 --> 00:16:09,200
But it's late now, so

284
00:16:09,280 --> 00:16:11,920
go to bed. We'll talk tomorrow. Mwah.

285
00:16:12,000 --> 00:16:14,360
Hey, Arnon. Arnon!

286
00:16:20,080 --> 00:16:21,480
<i>The number you dialed…</i>

287
00:17:54,880 --> 00:17:58,360
Didn't you sleep enough, Rat?
You look exhausted.

288
00:17:58,440 --> 00:18:00,080
Yes, Grandma.

289
00:18:00,160 --> 00:18:01,840
I had another strange dream last night.

290
00:18:02,480 --> 00:18:04,920
Again? What was it about this time?

291
00:18:05,000 --> 00:18:08,800
If you think it's nonsense,
you don't need to know

292
00:18:08,880 --> 00:18:09,960
what it was about.

293
00:18:10,040 --> 00:18:12,000
That's good then.

294
00:18:12,080 --> 00:18:14,640
You can stop paying attention to it.

295
00:18:14,720 --> 00:18:16,640
You're an adult now, Rat.

296
00:18:16,720 --> 00:18:18,640
An executive.

297
00:18:18,720 --> 00:18:20,320
A boss.

298
00:18:20,400 --> 00:18:24,040
Stop paying attention
to this kind of nonsense already.

299
00:18:24,640 --> 00:18:26,920
- Yes, Grandma.
- Good. I'm glad you understand.

300
00:18:27,000 --> 00:18:28,000
Thank you, dear.

301
00:18:32,440 --> 00:18:33,960
- Grandma.
- Hm?

302
00:18:37,080 --> 00:18:42,400
If I were to ask to use Dad's office,

303
00:18:44,280 --> 00:18:45,440
what would you say?

304
00:18:45,520 --> 00:18:47,280
Why would I object?

305
00:18:47,360 --> 00:18:50,800
You already have
so much work at Vanich as it is.

306
00:18:50,880 --> 00:18:53,880
If it helps make things more convenient,

307
00:18:53,960 --> 00:18:56,240
you can decide for yourself, dear.

308
00:18:57,880 --> 00:18:59,440
- Thank you.
- Of course.

309
00:18:59,520 --> 00:19:01,520
So when do you plan to use the room?

310
00:19:01,600 --> 00:19:05,560
I'll have someone go in
and tidy up your father's belongings.

311
00:19:05,640 --> 00:19:08,600
That won't be necessary.
I want everything to stay where it is,

312
00:19:08,680 --> 00:19:12,520
as if Dad were still here with me.

313
00:19:17,520 --> 00:19:20,280
What did you say?
You want to replace the large trees

314
00:19:20,360 --> 00:19:22,000
with an open lawn and a rock garden?

315
00:19:22,080 --> 00:19:23,200
Yes.

316
00:19:24,520 --> 00:19:26,000
You have any objections, Mr. Supol?

317
00:19:26,080 --> 00:19:30,480
Uh, none at all. But today,
Ms. Kluay has to hand over the work.

318
00:19:30,560 --> 00:19:31,880
That's fine.

319
00:19:33,240 --> 00:19:34,840
I can

320
00:19:34,920 --> 00:19:37,400
keep assigning additional work.

321
00:19:37,480 --> 00:19:41,160
Yes, additional work is no problem.
I'll report this to Mrs. Wanee.

322
00:19:44,480 --> 00:19:45,600
With the utmost respect.

323
00:19:45,680 --> 00:19:47,640
- Yes?
- There's no need to report it.

324
00:19:47,720 --> 00:19:49,680
I have full authority now,

325
00:19:50,280 --> 00:19:53,280
the same as your Mrs. Wanee, okay?

326
00:19:53,880 --> 00:19:55,200
- Okay, sir.
- Okay.

327
00:19:58,920 --> 00:20:00,360
Mr. Supol, hello. Mr. Warat, hello.

328
00:20:01,440 --> 00:20:04,920
About the rock garden, please finalize
the budget for me urgently.

329
00:20:05,000 --> 00:20:07,560
I need to present it
to Accounting, Ms. Kluay.

330
00:20:07,640 --> 00:20:09,040
Ah, that's alright.

331
00:20:09,760 --> 00:20:12,080
I've already had her handle it.

332
00:20:12,880 --> 00:20:14,640
Excuse me? What did you say?

333
00:20:15,560 --> 00:20:17,720
Let's talk inside. Come on.

334
00:20:17,800 --> 00:20:19,320
With the utmost respect,

335
00:20:19,400 --> 00:20:22,200
no one is allowed inside,
especially outsiders. Mrs. Wanee's orders.

336
00:20:22,280 --> 00:20:23,760
She's not an outsider.

337
00:20:24,600 --> 00:20:25,520
She's my girlfriend.

338
00:20:25,600 --> 00:20:26,680
Huh?

339
00:20:30,640 --> 00:20:31,760
She's my girlfriend.

340
00:20:46,880 --> 00:20:48,760
Why did you tell Mr. Supol that?

341
00:20:49,320 --> 00:20:50,840
What if Mrs. Wanee finds out?

342
00:20:51,360 --> 00:20:52,720
It doesn't matter.

343
00:20:53,280 --> 00:20:55,800
That's good.
You'll help us uncover the truth

344
00:20:55,880 --> 00:20:59,680
about my mom, as my Grandma's
future granddaughter-in-law. Okay?

345
00:20:59,760 --> 00:21:01,840
Ugh, why are you so selfish?

346
00:21:01,920 --> 00:21:03,760
Ever think about
whether I'm okay with this?

347
00:21:03,840 --> 00:21:05,760
Or maybe I already have a boyfriend?

348
00:21:07,240 --> 00:21:08,520
You? A boyfriend?

349
00:21:10,440 --> 00:21:14,760
Why? What's so surprising about that?

350
00:21:14,840 --> 00:21:17,880
I just don't want a boyfriend.

351
00:21:17,960 --> 00:21:19,880
That doesn't mean
no one's interested in me.

352
00:21:19,960 --> 00:21:21,920
That's your answer.
You don't have a boyfriend.

353
00:21:22,000 --> 00:21:23,480
Oh, Mr. Warat.

354
00:21:25,240 --> 00:21:26,760
You're impossible.

355
00:21:26,840 --> 00:21:29,640
Come on. Just get through this job.

356
00:21:29,720 --> 00:21:32,520
Once it's over,
everything goes back to normal.

357
00:21:32,600 --> 00:21:34,880
If I hadn't promised Ms. Mysterious,

358
00:21:34,960 --> 00:21:36,720
I would've run away from you already.

359
00:21:37,720 --> 00:21:39,200
What kind of man are you?
Do you have friends?

360
00:21:39,280 --> 00:21:42,040
Same goes for you.
Do you even have any friends?

361
00:21:42,120 --> 00:21:43,160
Mr. Warat.

362
00:21:43,240 --> 00:21:47,200
Okay, okay, enough. If we get any louder,

363
00:21:47,280 --> 00:21:49,480
Mr. Supol will hear us
and everything will be exposed.

364
00:21:50,080 --> 00:21:51,360
Then it'll all fall apart.

365
00:21:51,880 --> 00:21:54,760
Let's just tolerate it
until this mission is over.

366
00:21:54,840 --> 00:21:57,200
Who could ever tolerate someone like you?

367
00:21:57,280 --> 00:21:58,480
You're sure?

368
00:22:01,400 --> 00:22:02,560
Last night,

369
00:22:04,920 --> 00:22:06,800
I dreamed about Ms. Mysterious again.

370
00:22:06,880 --> 00:22:10,680
She took me into the office.

371
00:22:12,520 --> 00:22:14,000
And then…

372
00:22:14,080 --> 00:22:16,480
There were documents
flying everywhere, right?

373
00:22:17,520 --> 00:22:18,440
Hey.

374
00:22:19,360 --> 00:22:20,320
How did you know?

375
00:22:21,000 --> 00:22:23,640
This morning, I was half-asleep,

376
00:22:23,720 --> 00:22:24,720
and I saw it.

377
00:22:25,360 --> 00:22:28,880
I saw what looked like an office,

378
00:22:28,960 --> 00:22:32,120
with documents scattered everywhere.
Then suddenly, things went blank.

379
00:22:41,080 --> 00:22:42,440
Yes, Mr. Arnon?

380
00:22:44,840 --> 00:22:46,000
You actually believe that?

381
00:22:49,080 --> 00:22:50,160
Mr. Arnon called.

382
00:22:51,080 --> 00:22:54,280
He believes Dad's death…

383
00:22:56,240 --> 00:22:58,240
was intentional, that someone caused it.

384
00:22:58,320 --> 00:22:59,600
What?

385
00:23:21,800 --> 00:23:24,240
Aren't you going to apologize?

386
00:23:24,320 --> 00:23:27,040
You're the one who should apologize.
You're lucky it didn't stain.

387
00:23:27,120 --> 00:23:30,440
Didn't stain? Are you blind? Look.

388
00:23:30,520 --> 00:23:32,480
You messed yourself up
and still have the nerve to yell?

389
00:23:34,200 --> 00:23:35,840
You and your sister…

390
00:23:37,360 --> 00:23:40,480
are still the same.
Always wrong, never admitting it.

391
00:23:40,560 --> 00:23:42,840
What? How did your parents teach you?

392
00:23:43,680 --> 00:23:46,120
- Or did they never teach you anything?
- Hey!

393
00:23:46,200 --> 00:23:47,520
Dragging parents into this now?

394
00:23:47,600 --> 00:23:49,800
Stay out of my life.

395
00:23:49,880 --> 00:23:51,360
Do you understand?

396
00:23:51,440 --> 00:23:53,080
If you still want to work here.

397
00:23:53,680 --> 00:23:56,440
Go ahead. What are you going to do to me?
I'm not afraid of you.

398
00:23:56,520 --> 00:23:58,040
Barking like a little dog.

399
00:23:58,120 --> 00:23:59,000
You…

400
00:24:00,800 --> 00:24:03,080
You… Jirasin!

401
00:24:05,600 --> 00:24:07,440
Kluay Boonsita,

402
00:24:07,520 --> 00:24:10,520
my architect, is dating Warat?

403
00:24:11,120 --> 00:24:12,240
Yes, ma'am.

404
00:24:13,200 --> 00:24:14,920
How is that even possible?

405
00:24:15,000 --> 00:24:17,840
They've only met a few times.

406
00:24:18,440 --> 00:24:20,280
And a woman like Kluay,

407
00:24:20,360 --> 00:24:23,480
I can tell she's not the flirtatious type.

408
00:24:24,440 --> 00:24:26,280
And Rat? Oh my.

409
00:24:26,360 --> 00:24:29,400
In all these years, I've never
seen him interested in any woman.

410
00:24:29,480 --> 00:24:31,280
With the utmost respect,

411
00:24:31,360 --> 00:24:33,760
I find it strange too, ma'am.

412
00:24:35,400 --> 00:24:36,560
But let them be.

413
00:24:37,320 --> 00:24:38,920
Let them date for now.

414
00:24:39,000 --> 00:24:42,080
Kluay doesn't seem like a bad woman.

415
00:24:42,680 --> 00:24:45,480
Besides, how long could it possibly last?

416
00:24:45,560 --> 00:24:48,840
Kids these days
get together and break up in a flash.

417
00:24:48,920 --> 00:24:51,840
But maybe it's not such a bad thing.
If they're dating,

418
00:24:51,920 --> 00:24:55,480
we can persuade her
to stay and work with us at Vanich.

419
00:24:55,560 --> 00:24:57,160
Would that be a good idea, ma'am?

420
00:24:57,240 --> 00:24:58,800
Do you remember

421
00:24:58,880 --> 00:25:01,880
when you asked me
to investigate Ms. Kluay's work history?

422
00:25:03,480 --> 00:25:06,200
Oh yes, I remember.

423
00:25:06,280 --> 00:25:08,760
But when I decided
not to hire her long-term,

424
00:25:08,840 --> 00:25:10,120
I lost interest.

425
00:25:10,200 --> 00:25:12,760
Her work history looks rather odd, ma'am.

426
00:25:12,840 --> 00:25:15,680
She never stays at one place for long.

427
00:25:15,760 --> 00:25:18,440
Why? What happened?

428
00:25:18,520 --> 00:25:21,640
People say she's kind of strange.

429
00:25:21,720 --> 00:25:24,400
That she dabbles in things,
white magic, black magic, ma'am.

430
00:25:26,080 --> 00:25:27,800
Is that all?

431
00:25:27,880 --> 00:25:29,120
That doesn't sound true.

432
00:25:29,200 --> 00:25:31,200
Probably just gossip.

433
00:25:31,280 --> 00:25:34,040
In this day and age,
how could things like that even exist?

434
00:25:34,120 --> 00:25:37,080
With the utmost respect, if it is true,

435
00:25:37,160 --> 00:25:38,720
it plays right into Mr. Warat's situation.

436
00:25:38,800 --> 00:25:42,520
It would help him find out
why he keeps dreaming about Ms. Ampha.

437
00:25:46,560 --> 00:25:47,800
Sorry, ma'am.

438
00:25:47,880 --> 00:25:51,440
I'm worried about Mr. Warat,
so I slipped that name out.

439
00:25:51,520 --> 00:25:55,360
Don't ever mention this in front of Warat.

440
00:25:55,960 --> 00:25:57,000
Yes, ma'am.

441
00:25:58,160 --> 00:26:00,240
But still,

442
00:26:00,320 --> 00:26:03,720
thank you, Supol, for looking out for Rat.

443
00:26:04,360 --> 00:26:05,280
Yes, ma'am

444
00:26:05,360 --> 00:26:07,880
But as for Warat and Kluay,

445
00:26:07,960 --> 00:26:10,920
if I try to stop them
from seeing each other now,

446
00:26:11,000 --> 00:26:13,800
it'll look like
I'm getting overly defensive.

447
00:26:14,320 --> 00:26:16,160
Let's keep an eye on them
from a distance for now.

448
00:26:16,240 --> 00:26:17,520
Yes, ma'am.

449
00:26:17,600 --> 00:26:19,400
And those photos of that woman

450
00:26:19,480 --> 00:26:22,240
at the rose arbor house,
you've taken care of all of them, right?

451
00:26:22,320 --> 00:26:24,000
I've handled everything, ma'am.

452
00:26:24,800 --> 00:26:26,000
Then,

453
00:26:26,520 --> 00:26:30,480
tomorrow, take me to pay respects
to the monk at the temple.

454
00:26:30,560 --> 00:26:31,880
Yes, ma'am.

455
00:26:32,800 --> 00:26:34,320
I don't know

456
00:26:34,400 --> 00:26:39,840
when all these terrible things
will finally let go of my life.

457
00:26:41,040 --> 00:26:42,200
Ampha…

458
00:26:42,920 --> 00:26:45,600
What do you want from me?

459
00:26:50,400 --> 00:26:52,840
Our people went to collect

460
00:26:53,840 --> 00:26:56,080
Mr. Wichan's insurance documents
at the hospital.

461
00:26:56,160 --> 00:27:00,600
And how are these photos related
to my Dad's death? I don't understand.

462
00:27:02,560 --> 00:27:04,160
My style has always been

463
00:27:04,240 --> 00:27:08,040
to act first, prepare in advance,
because you never know what might happen.

464
00:27:09,520 --> 00:27:13,560
So, I checked the hospital's CCTV footage.

465
00:27:14,640 --> 00:27:18,080
Every camera, every angle, I got them all.

466
00:27:18,160 --> 00:27:20,200
And I took screenshots.

467
00:27:20,720 --> 00:27:25,160
There were many people who went to visit
Mr. Wichan at the hospital,

468
00:27:26,320 --> 00:27:28,400
until I came across one person

469
00:27:29,160 --> 00:27:31,400
and I kept this photo.

470
00:27:40,240 --> 00:27:41,360
Mr. Sarut?

471
00:27:41,440 --> 00:27:43,960
Why did he never tell me
that he went to visit my dad?

472
00:27:44,040 --> 00:27:46,200
That's exactly what we're questioning.

473
00:27:46,280 --> 00:27:48,240
Why he went to the hospital,

474
00:27:48,320 --> 00:27:51,280
why he avoided every CCTV camera,

475
00:27:51,360 --> 00:27:52,960
and why he didn't tell you.

476
00:28:00,720 --> 00:28:03,280
Why… Why are you two looking at me?

477
00:28:03,880 --> 00:28:06,880
Is this what Ms. Mysterious warned you
not to talk about?

478
00:28:06,960 --> 00:28:08,160
Not at all.

479
00:28:08,240 --> 00:28:10,320
I never saw anything at the hospital.

480
00:28:10,400 --> 00:28:14,360
And like I said, I never saw
your father in any of my visions.

481
00:28:14,960 --> 00:28:18,360
If it were serious enough to be murder,
why would we just let it slide?

482
00:28:19,080 --> 00:28:21,840
Let's stay calm first.
We're only suspicious at this point.

483
00:28:22,880 --> 00:28:24,600
There's something I want to tell you.

484
00:28:24,680 --> 00:28:27,600
Before Mr. Sarut visited Mr. Wichan,

485
00:28:28,120 --> 00:28:30,680
Mr. Wichan's condition was stable,

486
00:28:31,240 --> 00:28:34,320
slowly improving.
But after Mr. Sarut visited,

487
00:28:34,400 --> 00:28:36,360
just one night later,

488
00:28:36,440 --> 00:28:40,280
Mr. Wichan went into shock
and passed away.

489
00:28:41,640 --> 00:28:42,880
I'm going to go see him.

490
00:28:42,960 --> 00:28:45,080
Uh, Mr. Warat, calm down.

491
00:28:45,160 --> 00:28:47,760
Shouldn't we think this through
carefully together?

492
00:28:47,840 --> 00:28:49,120
There's nothing to think about.

493
00:28:49,200 --> 00:28:51,560
People like that, if they're lying,

494
00:28:51,640 --> 00:28:53,440
you can tell just by talking to them.

495
00:28:53,520 --> 00:28:55,360
Maybe we should slow down.

496
00:28:55,440 --> 00:28:59,680
Like I said, we're only suspicious.
He's not a murderer yet,

497
00:28:59,760 --> 00:29:02,040
it just smells strange, that's all.

498
00:29:02,120 --> 00:29:03,080
Why wait?

499
00:29:04,160 --> 00:29:06,200
- Come on, Kluay. Come with me.
- Where to?

500
00:29:06,280 --> 00:29:08,840
To his house.
We'll use your visions to catch him lying.

501
00:29:08,920 --> 00:29:11,160
But Sin is staying at Mr. Sarut's house.

502
00:29:11,240 --> 00:29:14,400
How many times have I told you
not to be afraid of Jirasin?

503
00:29:14,480 --> 00:29:17,680
Even better, everyone's there together.

504
00:29:18,280 --> 00:29:20,320
We'll catch them all lying at once.
Let's go.

505
00:29:21,840 --> 00:29:23,040
Help…

506
00:29:26,680 --> 00:29:27,600
Hey…

507
00:29:31,960 --> 00:29:33,720
Jirasin, you bastard.

508
00:29:33,800 --> 00:29:36,440
Look. I had to spend money
buying all new clothes.

509
00:29:40,840 --> 00:29:42,200
- Excuse me.
- Yes?

510
00:29:42,280 --> 00:29:44,600
Um, there's no hook in the restroom.

511
00:29:44,680 --> 00:29:46,000
Could you pass me my clothes, please?

512
00:29:46,080 --> 00:29:47,720
- Oh, sure.
- Thank you.

513
00:29:51,400 --> 00:29:53,720
Look at this. It's all stained.

514
00:29:54,600 --> 00:29:55,720
Ugh.

515
00:29:56,280 --> 00:29:58,160
Will this even wash out?

516
00:30:01,480 --> 00:30:03,720
Excuse me, could you pass me my clothes?

517
00:30:06,000 --> 00:30:08,080
My clothes please.

518
00:30:08,160 --> 00:30:10,000
Of course, dear.

519
00:30:10,080 --> 00:30:12,600
You want new clothes, right?

520
00:30:17,160 --> 00:30:18,960
What the hell are you doing, Ameena?

521
00:30:19,040 --> 00:30:20,560
Give me my clothes back right now.

522
00:30:20,640 --> 00:30:24,920
Oh wow, you even recognized my voice.

523
00:30:25,000 --> 00:30:27,800
How adorable, little rotten Som.

524
00:30:27,880 --> 00:30:30,920
Don't let me get out there. You're dead.

525
00:30:31,560 --> 00:30:33,480
So good at threatening, huh?

526
00:30:33,560 --> 00:30:36,040
Then feel free to stay inside
as long as you like.

527
00:30:36,120 --> 00:30:37,400
You foul-mouthed brat.

528
00:30:37,480 --> 00:30:40,640
You're the crazy old hag.
If you're so tough, fight me face-to-face.

529
00:30:40,720 --> 00:30:43,080
You're always acting like a sneaky dog.

530
00:30:43,160 --> 00:30:45,800
Give me my clothes back right now.
Give them back.

531
00:30:45,880 --> 00:30:48,680
Why don't you go pray
to whatever spirits your sister keeps,

532
00:30:48,760 --> 00:30:50,120
maybe they'll help you.

533
00:30:50,640 --> 00:30:53,680
Ameena, give me my clothes back right now.

534
00:30:59,600 --> 00:31:01,160
Why are you doing this?

535
00:31:01,880 --> 00:31:04,960
So you really do keep spirits, huh?
How did you even get here?

536
00:31:06,320 --> 00:31:08,840
Good that you know. When are you
going to stop picking fights?

537
00:31:08,920 --> 00:31:10,400
Because I hate you.

538
00:31:17,560 --> 00:31:20,120
Why should I have to study
with a freak like this?

539
00:31:20,200 --> 00:31:24,240
So annoying, right? No tuition fees,

540
00:31:24,320 --> 00:31:26,600
yet she lives comfortably
like the rest of us.

541
00:31:31,200 --> 00:31:33,560
- Wanna have some fun?
- Sure.

542
00:31:37,560 --> 00:31:41,880
Kluay, the Asian Math results are out.

543
00:31:41,960 --> 00:31:43,400
You've made it to the final round.

544
00:31:43,480 --> 00:31:44,920
Really, teacher?

545
00:31:46,000 --> 00:31:47,840
Thank you so much.

546
00:31:56,560 --> 00:32:00,800
Being around you is good.
I end up going to the library often too.

547
00:32:01,720 --> 00:32:03,120
You're already good, you know.

548
00:32:03,200 --> 00:32:06,240
You got into this college on your own.
It has nothing to do with me at all.

549
00:32:11,240 --> 00:32:12,160
Can you hold my bag for a sec?

550
00:32:14,840 --> 00:32:16,240
My hands are full of books, Na.

551
00:32:21,800 --> 00:32:23,400
It's okay, I'll carry them myself.

552
00:32:27,920 --> 00:32:29,760
Oops, sorry.

553
00:32:37,640 --> 00:32:39,560
Sorry, didn't see it there.

554
00:32:45,200 --> 00:32:48,120
Here, take it. Stop talking to her.

555
00:32:49,440 --> 00:32:50,320
You crazy bitch!

556
00:32:50,400 --> 00:32:51,960
- That's enough.
- Let go. I'm gonna kill her.

557
00:32:52,040 --> 00:32:54,960
Why are you taking so long
in the restroom? Oh.

558
00:32:58,480 --> 00:32:59,640
Hello.

559
00:32:59,720 --> 00:33:00,960
You ran into each other in there?

560
00:33:01,480 --> 00:33:02,480
Let's go.

561
00:33:03,120 --> 00:33:04,320
You're dead!

562
00:33:04,840 --> 00:33:06,040
Nothing happened, huh?

563
00:33:06,120 --> 00:33:08,520
Stop it. Don't do anything here.

564
00:33:09,160 --> 00:33:10,320
This isn't fair at all.

565
00:33:11,640 --> 00:33:13,360
Didn't you see what I went through?

566
00:33:15,080 --> 00:33:17,880
These two sisters
didn't only splash water on me,

567
00:33:18,480 --> 00:33:20,200
they even locked me in the restroom.

568
00:33:21,000 --> 00:33:23,640
Good thing someone came to help.

569
00:33:23,720 --> 00:33:25,200
Oh…

570
00:33:25,280 --> 00:33:27,320
Poor thing.

571
00:33:27,400 --> 00:33:29,680
You started it.
Why don't you tell Mr. Warat that too?

572
00:33:29,760 --> 00:33:30,720
Enough.

573
00:33:31,720 --> 00:33:33,000
Have some shame.

574
00:33:33,080 --> 00:33:35,680
If my mall's reputation is damaged,

575
00:33:36,680 --> 00:33:37,880
I'll sue both of you.

576
00:33:40,400 --> 00:33:43,560
I will press charges against them as well.

577
00:33:43,640 --> 00:33:45,320
If you do anything to Kluay,

578
00:33:45,960 --> 00:33:47,600
it's the same as doing it to me.

579
00:33:51,760 --> 00:33:53,560
Because right now, we're dating.

580
00:33:57,120 --> 00:33:58,080
This girl?

581
00:34:11,040 --> 00:34:12,560
It should be around here, right?

582
00:34:12,639 --> 00:34:15,800
According to Mr. Arnon's location,
yes, around here.

583
00:34:16,679 --> 00:34:18,239
Uh, Mr. Warat,

584
00:34:18,320 --> 00:34:21,000
can we not go to Mr. Sarut's house today?

585
00:34:21,080 --> 00:34:22,719
I'm worried about Som.

586
00:34:22,800 --> 00:34:25,239
I already asked Arnon to look after her.

587
00:34:26,080 --> 00:34:28,480
You asked the Head of Legal, Mr. Arnon,

588
00:34:28,560 --> 00:34:30,920
to look after someone like Som?

589
00:34:31,000 --> 00:34:34,280
He's busy enough already. You can just

590
00:34:34,360 --> 00:34:37,719
drop me off here. I'll call a taxi
and go back to my sister myself.

591
00:34:37,800 --> 00:34:40,080
I chose Mr. Arnon.

592
00:34:40,159 --> 00:34:42,159
Try trusting other people for once.

593
00:34:43,480 --> 00:34:46,639
Fine. Then I'm not worried
about Som anymore.

594
00:34:47,199 --> 00:34:49,480
Now I'm worried about Mr. Arnon.

595
00:34:59,520 --> 00:35:00,640
What are you doing?

596
00:35:03,560 --> 00:35:08,040
Hatred is appeased by vengeance.
You're done for, you crazy Ameena.

597
00:35:08,120 --> 00:35:09,440
Hey, hey!

598
00:35:10,600 --> 00:35:11,680
Arnon.

599
00:35:11,760 --> 00:35:12,640
What are you doing?

600
00:35:13,280 --> 00:35:14,880
What should I be doing?

601
00:35:16,480 --> 00:35:17,440
I asked what you're doing.

602
00:35:18,240 --> 00:35:19,520
Nothing.

603
00:35:20,160 --> 00:35:21,560
You want me to call security?

604
00:35:21,640 --> 00:35:25,240
Well, uh… Alright.

605
00:35:27,600 --> 00:35:28,480
Hey.

606
00:35:28,560 --> 00:35:30,080
Are you puncturing her tires?

607
00:35:30,160 --> 00:35:36,160
If you knew what Ameena did to Kluay,
and how she keeps harassing us non-stop,

608
00:35:36,240 --> 00:35:38,000
this would still be too mild.

609
00:35:38,080 --> 00:35:41,400
There are so many other ways
to get back at her. Why use this method?

610
00:35:43,600 --> 00:35:44,640
Show me your other hand.

611
00:35:46,040 --> 00:35:47,160
Security.

612
00:35:47,760 --> 00:35:48,720
Ugh.

613
00:35:48,800 --> 00:35:49,840
Here.

614
00:35:55,120 --> 00:35:56,800
Are you going to puncture three tires?

615
00:35:56,880 --> 00:35:58,880
Not this car.

616
00:35:58,960 --> 00:36:01,120
It's the Head of Technical's car.

617
00:36:01,200 --> 00:36:02,240
Jirasin?

618
00:36:02,320 --> 00:36:06,000
That guy's the real problem. Everything
that happened today is because of him.

619
00:36:06,600 --> 00:36:08,840
Listen to me.

620
00:36:08,920 --> 00:36:11,920
If he gets back at you,
what are you going to do then?

621
00:36:14,320 --> 00:36:17,080
I'll drive you home. Give it here.

622
00:36:17,160 --> 00:36:19,280
- Enough. Stop.
- Where are you taking it, Arnon?

623
00:36:19,360 --> 00:36:20,720
- Go home.
- But

624
00:36:20,800 --> 00:36:22,440
- Come. I'll take you.
- I still… I had everything

625
00:36:22,520 --> 00:36:24,240
- planned out already.
- I'll take you home.

626
00:36:25,800 --> 00:36:27,600
How do you feel? Better?

627
00:36:28,840 --> 00:36:29,680
Yes.

628
00:36:30,200 --> 00:36:33,040
Your sister is something else. I like her.

629
00:36:33,120 --> 00:36:34,320
Oh.

630
00:36:34,400 --> 00:36:36,280
If you live like that all the time,

631
00:36:36,360 --> 00:36:38,560
how can you ever find peace?

632
00:36:38,640 --> 00:36:40,520
Mmm.

633
00:36:40,600 --> 00:36:42,840
What about people who keep
running away from problems

634
00:36:43,720 --> 00:36:45,120
like someone around here?

635
00:36:45,200 --> 00:36:47,560
In the end, you have to deal with
the same problems anyway.

636
00:36:47,640 --> 00:36:49,840
You're right. I admit it.

637
00:36:49,920 --> 00:36:53,400
But we don't have to respond
with violence.

638
00:36:53,480 --> 00:36:55,640
If they come at us hard,

639
00:36:55,720 --> 00:36:57,560
we just hit back hard. That's fair.

640
00:36:58,160 --> 00:36:59,120
Right.

641
00:36:59,920 --> 00:37:01,560
So,

642
00:37:01,640 --> 00:37:04,000
you're determined
to go to Mr. Sarut's house?

643
00:37:24,600 --> 00:37:26,640
- Sin.
- Shall we go in?

644
00:37:28,640 --> 00:37:31,560
Uh… Can we not go in today?
I don't want to see Sin.

645
00:37:34,000 --> 00:37:37,040
Even if you wait
for Mr. Sarut and his wife,

646
00:37:37,640 --> 00:37:39,520
you'll still run into Sin anyway.

647
00:37:39,600 --> 00:37:43,320
Then, can we come another day?
A day when Sin isn't home?

648
00:37:44,240 --> 00:37:46,640
Kluay, what are you so afraid of?

649
00:37:47,240 --> 00:37:48,880
I'm not afraid, but,

650
00:37:49,760 --> 00:37:52,280
I'm really exhausted today.

651
00:37:52,360 --> 00:37:54,120
And if I have to see Sin,

652
00:37:54,200 --> 00:37:56,560
and then use my energy to see my vision,

653
00:37:56,640 --> 00:37:58,360
aren't you afraid I might die?

654
00:38:09,320 --> 00:38:11,160
Oh, Mr. Warat?

655
00:38:13,040 --> 00:38:14,440
- Hello.
- Hello.

656
00:38:14,520 --> 00:38:16,440
Please come in. Come inside.

657
00:38:22,400 --> 00:38:24,560
Kluay ran into Jirasin
at Mr. Sarut's house.

658
00:38:24,640 --> 00:38:26,320
What did he do to her?

659
00:38:26,920 --> 00:38:28,560
From now on,
we have to be much more careful.

660
00:38:28,640 --> 00:38:29,520
NEXT EPISODE

661
00:38:29,600 --> 00:38:32,760
Don't let Mrs. Wanee feel like we're
on the opposite side from her grandson.

662
00:38:32,840 --> 00:38:35,680
I hate secrets. I hate lies.

663
00:38:36,560 --> 00:38:39,520
I think the person
who can give you the best answers

664
00:38:40,160 --> 00:38:41,040
is Mrs. Wanee.

665
00:38:41,640 --> 00:38:43,720
<i>You don't love me anymore.</i>
<i>I don't love you either.</i>

666
00:38:43,800 --> 00:38:44,920
Why keep holding on?

667
00:38:45,000 --> 00:38:46,880
So you won't go back to Kluay.

668
00:41:14,480 --> 00:41:16,480
Subtitle translation by: Panuwat Baikeawon
